00:24:46.481 --> 00:24:46.980
cold.

00:24:46.980 --> 00:24:53.360
So maybe, just maybe, that
could be also inhabited there.

00:24:53.360 --> 00:24:54.770
It's potentially habitable.

00:24:54.770 --> 00:24:57.790
Whether there's life is
another complete question.

00:24:57.790 --> 00:25:01.190
But we have the
technological means

00:25:01.190 --> 00:25:03.440
to actually figure this out.

00:25:03.440 --> 00:25:04.940
And whatever else
you might think

00:25:04.940 --> 00:25:09.540
is going wrong in our life,
this is not one of these things.

00:25:09.540 --> 00:25:14.370
We are the explorers of
our centuries, I would say.

00:25:14.370 --> 00:25:16.830
And I'm sure it was
great for Columbus

00:25:16.830 --> 00:25:20.040
to actually find the New World.

00:25:20.040 --> 00:25:22.570
But we have an S on him.

00:25:22.570 --> 00:25:26.570
We have new worlds,
thousands of new worlds

00:25:26.570 --> 00:25:29.180
