learning about the atmosphere

00:49:06.540 --> 00:49:09.330
of a planet like this and keep
an open mind about what exactly

00:49:09.330 --> 00:49:12.090
the signal is that
we're trying to see.

00:49:12.090 --> 00:49:16.110
So not-- so more
specifically, not just the I

00:49:16.110 --> 00:49:19.360
want to detect oxygen on
an exact earth analog.

00:49:19.360 --> 00:49:19.860
- Right.

00:49:19.860 --> 00:49:21.510
But let me push on that a bit.

00:49:21.510 --> 00:49:30.580
So Lisa, you showed all this
kind of great diversity of life

00:49:30.580 --> 00:49:31.360
on the earth.

00:49:31.360 --> 00:49:33.749
The truth is when we are
designing our experiments

00:49:33.749 --> 00:49:35.290
to go and look for
life, we're really

00:49:35.290 --> 00:49:38.020
looking for life that's
identical to that on the earth.

00:49:38.020 --> 00:49:40.000
I mean, it's got to
be a rocky planet.

00:49:40.000 --> 00:49:41.500
It's got to be the
same temperature.

00:49:41.500 --> 00:49:43.540
It's got to have
oxygen and methane

00:49:43.540 --> 00:49:45.430
and water in the atmosphere.

00:49:45.430 --> 00:49:51.190
