00:49:55.210 --> 00:49:57.430
life that was fundamentally
different than life

00:49:57.430 --> 00:49:59.440
on the earth?

00:49:59.440 --> 00:50:01.740
Is that something that
we could aspire to do?

00:50:01.740 --> 00:50:04.300
Are we basically shackled
in that, we could only

00:50:04.300 --> 00:50:06.550
ever recognize life that's
so similar to the earth

00:50:06.550 --> 00:50:08.510
that that's the only
thing we can look for?

00:50:08.510 --> 00:50:11.120
- So I think there's two
parts of that answer.

00:50:11.120 --> 00:50:15.220
And one part is that what
we learn from planets

00:50:15.220 --> 00:50:16.929
is that they are very diverse.

00:50:16.929 --> 00:50:18.970
So what you don't want to
do, what you definitely

00:50:18.970 --> 00:50:22.570
don't want to do is
basically limit yourself to,

00:50:22.570 --> 00:50:25.750
let's say, with this one,
I can find one molecule,

00:50:25.750 --> 00:50:28.180
because I've now put all
my eggs in the basket

00:50:28.180 --> 00:50:30.510
that oxygen is what
will define life,

00:50:30.510 --> 00:50:33.700
because we'll figure out oxygen
you can make by splitting water

00:50:33.700 --> 00:50:35.470
or by splitting CO2.

00:50:35.470 --> 00:50:39.310
So giving you the
context is key.

00:50:39.310 --> 00:50:43.450
And so if you can get as
much wavelength as you can,

00:50:43.450 --> 00:50:45.700
that is your first information.

00:50:45.700 --> 00:50:50.160
Split the light as far from one
side to the other as you can.

00:50:50.160 --> 00:50:52.570
Get some information
on the temperature,

