the answer on which
of our closest stars

00:51:29.800 --> 00:51:32.140
have potentially
habitable world.

00:51:32.140 --> 00:51:34.300
I think the key
thing in science is

00:51:34.300 --> 00:51:36.130
that we developing our tools.

00:51:36.130 --> 00:51:39.220
And we'll always want to
have one big thing that

00:51:39.220 --> 00:51:42.550
can do a lot, but we need
to keep it, I would say,

00:51:42.550 --> 00:51:44.650
wavelengths [INAUDIBLE]
or energy wise as wide

00:51:44.650 --> 00:51:48.589
as we can and then have these
complimentary small missions.

00:51:48.589 --> 00:51:50.380
And the second point
